data.document: Unspecified vulnerability in HP Insight Control for Linux (aka IC-Linux or ICE-LX) 2.11 and earlier allows local users to gain privileges via unknown vectors.

data.name: CVE-2010-1909
data.document: Buffer overflow in the RunCmd method in the SdcUser.TgConCtl ActiveX control in tgctlcm.dll in Consona Live Assistance, Dynamic Agent, and Subscriber Assistance allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via vectors involving "CreateProcess params." NOTE: some of these details are obtained from third party information.

data.name: CVE-2010-0540
data.document: Cross-site request forgery (CSRF) vulnerability in the web interface in CUPS before 1.4.4, as used on Apple Mac OS X 10.5.8, Mac OS X 10.6 before 10.6.4, and other platforms, allows remote attackers to hijack the authentication of administrators for requests that change settings.
